Local Testing installations:

Dependencies:
sudo apt-get install liblingua-en-inflect-perl

Copy a live database (probably the easiest) or run any outstanding migrations off of a skeleton database.

Symlink or copy files:
SAMPLEhtaccess > deploy/www/.htaccess
../docs/tchalvakSAMPLEresources.php > resources.php (if symlinking, symlink from within /deploy/)
docs/gitignoreSAMPLE > .gitignore
docs/robots.txt > deploy/www/robots.txt

Add a /compiled/ directory to match the path to compiled specified in the resources, and make it web writable.
(e.g. mkdir templates/compiled, chmod 777 templates/compiled )

Make sure that, for the .htaccess file to work:
#The AllowOverride directive in /etc/apache2/sites-available/default
#cannot equal None, as that will prevent the .htaccess from working.

